Royal Copenhagen


                    World-famous Royal Copenhagen was founded in 1775 under the protection from the widow queen Juliane Marie, then called The Royal Porcelain Factory. Royal Copenhagen is today one of Europe's oldest porcelain manufacturers and is known the world over for their high quality and beautiful design. 
                    Read more �


